 Description:
The position property controls how an element is positioned on the page. Common values:

static (default)

relative

absolute

fixed

sticky




<!DOCTYPE html>
<html>
<head>
  <title>Position Property</title>
  <style>
    .relative-box {
      position: relative;
      top: 20px;
      left: 30px;
      background-color: #ffd166;
      padding: 15px;
      width: 200px;
      border: 2px solid #f4a261;
    }

    .absolute-box {
      position: absolute;
      top: 50px;
      right: 20px;
      background-color: #06d6a0;
      padding: 15px;
      width: 180px;
      border: 2px solid #1b9aaa;
      color: white;
    }

    .container {
      position: relative;
      height: 200px;
      border: 2px solid #555;
      margin-top: 40px;
    }
  </style>
</head>
<body>

  <h2>13. Position Property</h2>

  <div class="relative-box">
    This box is <strong>relative</strong> positioned (offset from normal position).
  </div>

  <div class="container">
    <div class="absolute-box">
      This box is <strong>absolute</strong> positioned inside container.
    </div>
  </div>

</body>
</html>
